##After a family of eight got infected

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

Goggles outside a hospital. China Youth Daily, China Youth Daily, photo by Li Qiang

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Yang Jie, China Youth Daily

Editor | from Yuhua

One accident after another. Three days before the Spring Festival, Wei Beibei's father began to have a fever, the next day is the mother, the third day, the turn of Wei Beibei.

Fourth, fifth, sixth, in-laws, younger brother and two sisters fever, should be in the round table of a family of eight, lying in different hospital beds to fight for life.

On Feb. 13, Wei Beibei's husband, the only healthy adult left in the family, developed symptoms and his 11-month-old baby daughter began coughing.

The hospital said the baby had pneumonia!

A thriving family can not find a "healthy person" to look after the children. She's in all kinds of groups, texting for help.

1

This Spring Festival holiday, if no accident, they are lying on the beach basking in the Western Pacific Ocean. Wei Beibei, a 38-year-old father and daughter, and her husband to start a business, take the project, living in a european-style decoration of a large house in Wuhan, the family travels three times a year.

"Who would have thought the disease would be so close to me? " Said Weibei.

On January 29, the family checked into the Foshan Zuoling community service and Health Center in Wuhan. February 2, the mother's condition deteriorated, in a coma, was transferred to the Golden Pool Hospital, two critically ill. Father in the next day to Wuhan Tongji Hospital in the new town of France, cell phone turned in, lost contact, little sister followed to the same hospital, easy to care.

Wei was then transferred to the Hubei Provincial People's Hospital, where he was given oxygen treatment. She was transferred to Wuhan's Third Hospital, Guanggu district. Only the younger brother is in a mild condition and has been staying at the fozuoling community service health center.

The father-in-law and mother-in-law were separated at home, and later admitted to the converted Shelter Hospital of Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center. There was a flourishing festival years ago, and now rows of patients with mild illness are packed in.

Eight people were scattered in six hospitals in Wuhan.

The mother's condition is the most worrying. She's already sick, high blood pressure, diabetes, thyroid surgery. She lay curled up in her hospital bed, feverish and weak, coughing every time she lay down, only to sit up and cough again.

Before she was transferred to the hospital, she said to the child weakly, "please, let the doctor give me an injection and let me go quickly. I am so sick. " Her four children are suffering from the same disease as her, and the old man is afraid that he will not see his children one last time, reluctantly, he was wheeled into an ambulance. Upon arriving at the Golden Pool Hospital, my mother began to cough up blood, and the next day it got worse.

Someone died in the ICU, my mother said, off and on. Someone across the hall, who had less symptoms than herself, had been seen fetching water yesterday and died this morning.

From his bed in another hospital, Weibeibei listened to his mother's faint breath and fear, surrounded by a cacophony of coughing. She thought of the death of Dr. Li Wenliang in Wuhan. "Such a young man and a doctor, and to think of my parents, they might not survive... "

She calls her mother every day to encourage her, dare not video, afraid of her mother to see their own look bad. His mother was too weak to speak, and he said to the receiver alone, "you must get well. We need you in this family. "

Every year, the mother helped the children to prepare the new year goods, meat round son, their own pickled fish, divided into 4 to each family, "New Year to have flavor. ".

Every holiday children sit around, eating mother never let the children clean up, brothers and sisters wipe mouth, sit chat.

My mother was dying, my father was out of touch, and my siblings were stuck in their beds, unable to move. "How could this family have suffered so much? " Weibei thought.

The cities and towns of Hubei were blockaded one by one. It was snowing in Wuhan. Wei Beibei had no grand dreams before going to bed. Her wish was simple. She just wanted her mother to live.

Before the Spring Festival, this family is busy for the new year, buying New Year goods, fried dumplings. At the end of the year, Weibeibei's father caught a common cold, and his mother accompanied him to the hospital, without a mask.

Late that night, Weibeibei received a call from his parents, "why are so many people in the hospital today" . 57-year-old parents waited in line for six hours. It is likely that at that time, they became the undifferentiated hosts of the new coronavirus.

2

On February 13, Weibei's cell phone rang again. On the other end of the phone, her husband said he was "weak in the limbs and weak in the body. " To make matters worse, the 11-month-old baby started coughing and went to the hospital to be checked. Darling had pneumonia.

It was not clear whether it was common pneumonia or new crown pneumonia, but the family of eight had been diagnosed and the baby's condition was worrying. Weibeibei came home from his mother's home the same day holding the baby, the nanny returned home for the New Year, she and darling contact the most.

"I cried so much that I had to be treated for any kind of pneumonia, " Weibei said. "It's a disease that changes so quickly that the child can't wait. " The hospital prescribed medication, but no treatment was available.

That night, she begged people, "I have friends in the hospital, but they can't even get into a hospital themselves because they're sick. " She asked friends to post on the Internet, and didn't hang up until 2 a.m. Afraid of disturbing the other patients in the same room, she put her cell phone on mute, staring into tears until dawn.

Wei Beibei originally a week without a fever, but that day temperature, four times are 37.5 Â°C. Her lungs hurt, her throat and eyes were bitter, and every time she coughed, her body ached like a sprint after a 100-meter race. She was stuck at the head of the bed, unable to take a step forward, and her cell phone was her only contact with the outside world.

She stared at the screen light up, dark, monitor "beep" to ring, she could not sleep. She told reporters that at the time she remembered her mother's home table is rectangular, on top of a round board. Every weekend, the family's regular program is to go to his mother's house for dinner, sometimes the grandson to catch up on classes, the mother always said, "rare, also catch up, the class closed. " Weibeibei disagreed, on weekdays, study is always more important than a table.

She thought of Happy Mediocrity, of the view of the East L. Green Road, of her son riding his bike, her husband taking pictures, of Weibei holding his daughter "crazy. ". In a relaxing video, the older brother plays the cello and the younger sister claps her hands and shakes her hips.

The father-in-law and the mother-in-law living in the shelter did not deteriorate, to daughter-in-law Call Comfort, "your illness has not recovered for so long, is because of daily worry. "

The next day, Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital called: The baby can be admitted to hospital, but need a healthy adult to accompany.

At that time, the husband's test results have not come out, the large family can not find a "healthy person. ". The hospital kept pushing, promising to keep the beds until nightfall. Weibeibei did everything he could to get someone to take care of darling, from 2,000 yuan a day to 5,000 yuan, but no one answered.

3

At the same time, volunteers Tang Meng and Cui Zhiyuan saw Weibeibei's message asking for help in different groups. Tomon, 24, was studying bartending at a bar, with a flag on his motorcycle and a tattoo on his chest. Cui Zhiyuan, 29, whose husband and children are in their native Sichuan Province, works as a wine salesman in Wuhan.

They contacted Wei Beibei, offered to accompany the 11-month-old baby. Weibeibei told the truth, the child may have a new coronary pneumonia, the family of 8 people confirmed, please them to consider well. "think it through, " said the two volunteers. Choi Heard Wei Bei crying on the phone.

"It's very touching when someone gives their life to help you, " Weibeibei said earnestly. "When I get out of the hospital, I want to help people who need help. " Weibeibei transferred some money to express his gratitude, but neither of them accepted it. "It gets stale when you close it, " said Tomon.

"We don't know medicine, can only be a guerrilla, do some coolies. " Tang Meng said, his other skills have no, only a body strength. He joined a dozen volunteer groups, from the first busy to now, "or all day lying at home, uneasy. "

But he didn't dare tell his family he was taking care of a patient. She couldn't say that every time she looked after darling in the hospital, she would press a video from her home, saying she was sleeping or at a company meeting. "We are used to hospitals, but from the outside it looks very dangerous. "

The husband checked darling in and went to get his test results -- all normal, false alarm. The two volunteers take turns with the father to look after the baby.

Every morning, Cui Zhiyuan prepares the milk and dresses the baby before she wakes up. The nurses came to hang the water and do the atomization. They had to hold the baby for four or five hours. As soon as I put it down, darling cried. At this point, Choi always thought of her children. Had it not been for the outbreak, she would have met her seven-year-old son in Sichuan. After the New Year, she devoted herself almost entirely to volunteer work, selling alcohol and helping others in her circle of friends, and had little time to keep in touch with her family.

The flood of requests for help sent a shiver through her brain, and when she called to verify the information, Ms. Cui was always worried about losing hope. In the middle of the night in Wuhan, she sent a protective suit, a pair of goggles, a USB stick and a bottle of disinfectant. Sometimes she was exhausted, but the thought of "this thing will save his life" forced her to keep running.

Late One night, as she was getting ready to go to bed, an urgent request came for an hour and a half's drive from Hankou to Ezhou, with a note that said, "for money, you name your price. ".

This mold is the accessories of the shelter hospital trash can, looks like chopsticks, without it, the trash can can not leave the factory, so many people are waiting. Cui Zhiyuan did not ask for money, met four or five checkpoints on the road, staff heard her task, after reporting to the superior, all let go.

Unlike Cui, who drives a private car, Tang Meng rides a motorcycle to work as a Coolie, reaching speeds of 90 kilometers per hour. "It's impossible to do it in Wuhan during the daytime, " he said. He volunteers at the Red Cross's answer team, at first there were calls for donations from all over the place, and then there were calls of doubt. "If it was a personal call, I would have hung up on the blackout. But this is an official hotline and I can only explain, not talk back. "

Tang Meng spent the rest of his time helping move supplies and riding his motorcycle across the Yangtze River Bridge. Shipments from all over the country stopped at a highway junction in Wuhan. Behind the sand mounds and barricades, volunteers unload them from big lorries into cars, vans, minivans and transport them to hospitals and communities.

After taking care of the baby, Tom Suddenly turned into a "warm man" , he found out the home with the doll in the past. Every time he puts the kids to bed, he searches for "bedtime kids' favorite songs" on the music APP and plays them to darling.

From time to time, the two volunteers took videos of the children and sent them to Weibei, "to cheer her up, after all, she hasn't seen the children for more than 20 days. "

Wei Beibei's husband thanked the volunteers and told Tomon to ask for anything in the future. "I don't want to mix anything utilitarian with you, " said Tang Meng, who felt uneasy

That night, two men of more than 10 years of age were chatting in the baby ward until 4 a.m. , when the husband of Wei Beibei confided in him, "If I was infected and the baby wasn't, I would kneel down in front of someone who cared for my baby, and if my baby was infected and I wasn't, I would rush in front of the patient and infect myself and isolate myself with the baby, " said Tomon, who grew up in a single-parent home, it was both admiring and touching.

Wei Beibei has moved on. I used to work with my husband at the office, and I would have dinner at night instead of spending time with my kids. "I'm such a bad mother. ". She's decided to take care of the kids herself.

She was too busy to return to work, loss of money, wages, rent, these pressures she had nothing to do, just want to hurry home, embrace their families.

This Spring Festival family adventure made her understand that maybe luck is the real thing to settle down. She settled for a community hospital in the first place, a bed many people couldn't get. The four-story Community Hospital, built in 1952 and equipped with an inpatient department, is better equipped than most health stations for blood tests and CT scans. At the most difficult time, volunteers are willing to come over and give her a hand, she felt the family is lucky.

The wind in Wuhan brings a little warmth in winter. Good News after good news. On February 18, the sickest mother was the first to be discharged. That day, the father who did not hear from me just called to say that he had stopped taking medicine and would soon be able to go home. Big sister has been discharged from the hospital, younger sister, brother and in-law also entered the hospital before the countdown, leaving Weibei nucleic acid test or positive, but the symptoms have disappeared. The doctor said she "worry about this every day, comfort that, no one's phone call, in order to get better quickly. "

On New Year's Eve, the potted plants planted by Weibeibei came to life. She said her family was lucky, that there were people in the city who had lost their parents and their children. "My family got through this and decided to take a road trip to get away from it all. " When my daughter grows up, she will talk about the Spring Festival in 2020.

(at the request of the interviewee, Wei Beibei, Tang Meng and Cui Zhiyuan were given pseudonyms.)
